Prentiss M. BROWN, Administrator, Office of Price Administration, v. O. S. SHIRK. No. 2877. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. April 25, 1944. Fleming James, Jr., Director, Litigation Division,, and David London, Chief, Appellate Branch, Office of Price Administration, both of Washington, D. C., James B. Nash, Dist. Enforcement Atty., and A. D. Weiskirch and Ellis C. Clark, Litigation Attys., Office of Price Administration, all of Wichita, Kan., and David B. Love, Regional Litigation Atty., Office of Price Administration, of Dallas, Tex., for appellant. George McGill, of Wichita, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, BRATTON, and MURRAH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed pursuant to stipulation.
